  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Forge Unbreakable Passwords!\n\n\"password123\" — the most hacked password in the world. Let's fix that by building a tool that generates cryptographically strong passwords in Python.\n\n### What You'll Learn\n- `random` and `secrets` modules\n- String manipulation with `string` module\n- Function parameters with defaults\n- f-string formatting\n\n### Why This Matters\n- 81% of breaches are caused by weak passwords\n- A 16-character random password takes ~1 trillion years to crack\n- Your tool will be more useful than most apps on the App Store!\n\n> **Fun fact:** The `secrets` module uses your OS's cryptographic random number generator — making it truly unpredictable."
  },
